main event: Two star-shaped silver, green, and yellow objects were observed in the sky over Bedford, Indiana.
interesting points: The objects were observed for approximately two hours.
The objects were seen at 100 to 125 degrees azimuth and 18 degrees elevation, and 110 degrees azimuth and 50 degrees elevation.
The reporting officer concurred that the sighting was likely an astronomical phenomenon.
No photographs were available in the provided report.
The report concluded that the sighting was likely an astronomical phenomenon, but did not have sufficient data for a definitive evaluation.
